@@TJvXPButton
<TITLEIMG TJvXPButton>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.XPControls,JVCL.Buttons.Push
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Button drawn in an XP style.
Description
  Use TJvXPButton on your form when you need a button that has a themed XP look.

  TJvXPButton introduces properties to display an image on the button and arrange the images and text
  on the button.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomButton
Summary
  Base class for buttons that are drawn in an XP style.
Description
  Use TJvXPCustomButton as a base class for buttons that are drawn in an XP style.

  Do not create instances of TJvXPCustomButton. Use the generic descendant TJvXPButton, or create your
  own descendant class.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomButton.AutoGray
Summary
  Indicates whether to display the image of the button grayed when the button is not enabled.
Description
  Set AutoGray to true to render the image of the button grayed, when the button is not enabled.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomButton.Cancel
Summary
  Determines whether the button’s OnClick event handler executes when the Escape key is pressed.
Description
  If Cancel is True, the button’s OnClick event handler executes when the user presses Esc. Although an
  application can have more than one Cancel button, the form calls the OnClick event handler only for
  the first visible button in the tab order.
See Also
  OnClick

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomButton.Default
Summary
  Determines whether the button’s OnClick event handler executes when the Enter key is pressed.
Description
  If Default is True, the button’s OnClick event handler executes when the user presses Enter.

  Although an application can have more than one Default button, the form calls the OnClick event
  handler only for the first visible button in the tab order. Moreover, any button that has focus
  becomes the Default button temporarily; hence, if the user selects another button before pressing
  Enter, the selected button’s OnClick event handler executes instead.
See Also
  TJvXPCustomButton.Cancel

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomButton.Glyph
Summary
  Specifies the bitmap that appears on the button.
Description
  Use Glyph to specify the image to display on the button. The actual location of the image is
  controlled by the ayout property. In contrast to TBitBtn, Glyph can contain one image only but you
  can modify its run-time appearance by setting AutoGray to true.
See Also
  TJvXPCustomButton.AutoGray, TJvXPCustomButton.Layout

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomButton.Layout
Summary
  Indicates the location of Glyph on the button.
Description
  Use Layout to specify where you want the image to appear on the button in relation to the Caption.
See Also
  Caption

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomButton.ShowAccelChar
Summary
  Determines how an ampersand in the label text is displayed.
Description
  Set ShowAccelChar to True to allow the button to display an underlined accelerator key value. When
  ShowAccelChar is True, any character preceded by an ampersand (&) appears underlined.

  To display an ampersand when ShowAccelChar is True, use two ampersands (&&) to stand for the single
  ampersand that is displayed.

  Set ShowAccelChar to False to display the text with all ampersands appearing as ampersands.
See Also
  Caption

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomButton.ShowFocusRect
Summary
  Indicates whether the button is drawn with a focus rect when focused.
Description
  Use ShowFocusRect to specify whether a standard focus rect is drawn on the button when it has the
  focus.
See Also
  Focused

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomButton.SmoothEdges
Summary
  Indicates how the edges are drawn.
Description
  Use SmoothEdges to specify whether the edges of the button are drawn in a standard way or with color
  highlighting that makes the edges appear smoother.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomButton.Spacing
Summary
  Specifies the distance in pixels between the image and the text.
Description
  Use spacing to specify how many pixels separate the image in Glyph and the text in Caption.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomButton.WordWrap
Summary
  Determines whether the control inserts soft carriage returns so text wraps at the right margin.
Description
  Use WordWrap to specify how the text is drawn when it doesn't fit inside the control. If WordWrap is
  true, the text will be wrapped to as many lines as needed to fit the text inside the control.
See Also
  Caption

