@@TJvXPToolButton
<TITLEIMG TJvXPToolButton>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.XPControls,JVCL.Buttons.Push
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Button control that draws its client area using a predefined style.
Description
  Use TJvXPToolButton on your form when you need a button that looks like the caption buttons in
  Windows XP. A border icon button is a button located in the caption area of a form, like the
  minimize, maximize and restore buttons. TJvXPToolButton can also display some additional images.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPToolType
<TITLE TJvXPToolType type>
Summary
  Specifies the available button types for an XP tool button.
Description
  TJvXPToolType specifies the possible images that can be displayed in an XP tool button.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
